Spanish outlet La Razon have reported the Magpies are looking to strengthen their goalkeeping options and a highly ambitious move for the Slovenian international has been discussed. Oblak – a former team-mate of United star Kieran Trippier – joined Atleti in July 2014 and has gone on to become one of the world’s most consistent goalkeepers during his time in the Spanish capital. Trippier spoke about Oblak in a recent interview with the BBC, saying: “He is one of the best keepers in the world. Roman Abramovich Confirms He Will Sell Chelsea Tuchel Claims Chelsea Have Too Many Injury Worries To List “I think he would be unbelievable in the Premier League. Obviously, who could he go to, that’s the question? “I have had conversations with him about the Premier League, he has always asked me questions. Of course, I would love to see him in the Premier League. “You never know, you never know what could happen.” Timo Werner is reportedly set to leave Chelsea this summer – and Newcastle have been heavily linked with a move for the German international. Sky Germany have suggested the Magpies will face major competition from Bundesliga giants Borussia Dortmund, who see Werner as a possible replacement for Erling Haaland. RB Salzburg striker Karim Adeyemi is also said to be under consideration after scoring 14 goals in 18 games for the Austrian Bundesliga clubs. POLL Newcastle World revealed Fiorentina centre-back Nikola Milenkovic was on Newcastle’s radar during the January transfer window. However, the Magpies were not the only Premier League club interested in the Serbian international. Italian journalist Angelo Giorgetti has suggested West Ham United agreed a deal with Fiorentina and held talks with Milenkovic, who was not keen on a move to the Premier League and remained in Florence. He said: “I really don’t know. I can only say that Milenkovic is a high-level defender who rejected West Ham last summer – the deal was practically done – and is very close to Vlahovic.”